Looks like your scans use 4 MCA channels.  No info in the file about MCA configuration, just the raw data.

For sure, your data files were caught up in the change with 2016.0601.0.   A revised regular expression key for the MCA data will solve the problem.  Should be an easy fix.  Hope to get to it over the weekend.

The only tricky part will be how spec2nexus learns how many different MCA channels to use.  Here's what it looks like now.

    @A 0 0 ...     means only a single MCA is used
    @A1 0 0 ...    means this is data for MCA 1
    @A2 0 0 ...    means this is data for MCA 2

and so on, still not hard to implement, the regexp pattern changes from '@A' to '@A\d*' (that works!)

(ref: https://www.cheatography.com/davechild/cheat-sheets/regular-expressions/)

take a bit longer to put the channel number logic in the code

