Any child directive can ask for table controller, so then you can request for tableState

```Javascript
angular.directive('rowHighlighter',function(){
    return {
        require:'stTable',
        link:function(scope,element,attr){
                     scope.$watch(function () {
          return ctrl.tableState().sort;
        }, function (newValue) {
