@christian-oreilly @elisabettai @croessert #91 (merged) is a first towards making efeatures only calculate within the stimulus interval. There is now a setting called 'strict_stiminterval', which is set to False by default (for backward compatibility). You can change this setting by calling efel.setIntSetting("strict_stiminterval", strict). When True, the feature peak_indices will only returns the spikes inside the stimulus interval (and all the features that depend on this, like Spikecount, peak_time). 
I want to stress this is only a first step. Features like AHP_depth will now only look at spikes inside the interval, but if the AHP itself falls outside of the interval, it will still be reported. I will need to manually change these kind of other features too. Please create another ticket if you want specific features to be fixed.
I will also change BluePyOpt to allow you to specifiy the strict_stiminterval.

