I suggest creating a step that takes the environment variable into account. Here's an example:

```python
@step(r'I query "(?P<domain>\w+)" domain with the field "(?P<field>\w+)" equal-to the String "(?<value>\w+)')
def query_domain(domain, field, value):
    # ...

@step(r'I query "(?P<domain>\w+)" domain with the field "(?P<field>\w+)" equal-to the test variable')
def query_domain_env(domain, field):
    test_variable = os.getenv('TEST_VARIABLE', 2)
    query_domain(domain, field, test_variable)
```

